most critical phase is when price breaks

277
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:50,320
above the previous major swing high. If

278
00:11:47,519 --> 00:11:52,800
the price rises above this level on

279
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:55,360
higher volume compared to the previous

280
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:59,279
swing low, it confirms the shift in

281
00:11:55,360 --> 00:12:02,000
sentiment with buyers taking control.

282
00:11:59,279 --> 00:12:04,720
Conversely, in an uptrend with higher

283
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:07,519
highs and higher lows, when a price

284
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:10,160
breaks below a significant level, it

285
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:12,880
forms a new lower low, indicating a

286
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:14,800
potential trend reversal. From a price

287
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:17,040
action perspective, this pattern

288
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:20,000
indicates a loss of momentum from the

289
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:22,560
buyers. Instead of continuing to make

290
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:25,279
new higher highs, the price creates a

291
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:28,160
reversal pattern, suggesting a potential

292
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:30,480
shift in order flow. After a minor

293
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:33,600
pullback, if the price continues to

294
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:36,399
create lower lows and lower highs, it

295
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:39,360
indicates a new bearish trend. If the

296
00:12:36,399 --> 00:12:41,200
volume during this high point is lower

297
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:44,000
than the volume during the previous

298
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:45,920
swing high, it indicates a decrease in

299
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:48,560
buying interest and the possible

300
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:51,120
exhaustion of the uptrend. This decline

301
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:53,680
in volume serves as an initial warning

302
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:56,320
sign. You don't know yet if a reversal

303
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:58,480
is on the cards. However, the most

304
00:12:56,320 --> 00:13:01,839
crucial phase is when the price breaks

305
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:04,399
below this previous major swing low. If

306
00:13:01,839 --> 00:13:07,200
the price breaks this level and does so

307
00:13:04,399 --> 00:13:09,519
on higher volume compared to the volume

308
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:11,040
during the previous swing high, it

309
00:13:09,519 --> 00:13:14,079
confirms the shift in the market

310
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:16,240
sentiment. Buyers have taken control,

311
00:13:14,079 --> 00:13:18,240
further supporting the potential trend

312
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:20,399
reversal.

313
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:23,360
The head and shoulders pattern, although

314
00:13:20,399 --> 00:13:25,920
a retail one, is a decent one to monitor

315
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:28,959
as it marks the transition point between

316
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:31,519
an uptrend and a downtrend with the left

317
00:13:28,959 --> 00:13:33,519
side representing the end of the uptrend

318
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:36,000
and the right side representing the

319
00:13:33,519 --> 00:13:38,639
beginning of the downtrend. The pattern

320
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:41,519
starts as a series of higher highs and

321
00:13:38,639 --> 00:13:44,320
higher lows. That sequence is altered

322
00:13:41,519 --> 00:13:46,800
when a low point is formed that has the

323
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:49,600
same approximate values as the previous

324
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:52,480
low. If it contains a liquidity run,

325
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:54,959
it's even better. The price rallies from

326
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:57,600
this low point, but instead of resuming

327
00:13:54,959 --> 00:14:00,720
the sequence of higher highs, a lower

328
00:13:57,600 --> 00:14:04,240
high occurs. Then the price slides back

329
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:06,480
to the previous low for a third time. If

330
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:09,279
a higher high occurs on expanding

331
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:12,480
volume, this is considered healthy and

332
00:14:09,279 --> 00:14:14,880
normal in an uptrend. However, in an

333
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:17,760
ideal scenario, the head and shoulders

334
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:20,399
pattern sees volume diminish on each

335
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:22,720
successive high. The higher high that

336
00:14:20,399 --> 00:14:25,519
forms the highest point of the head

337
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:27,839
should ideally occur on lower volume

338
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:30,560
than the previous high which formed the

339
00:14:27,839 --> 00:14:33,120
left shoulder. Volume should diminish

340
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:36,160
further on the third high as the right

341
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:38,800
shoulder forms. This demonstrates a lack

342
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:41,360
of enthusiasm from the buyers who are

343
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:44,560
losing their will to continue buying at

344
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:47,600
higher prices. If and when the neckline

345
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:51,120
breaks, that break should occur on high

346
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:54,000
volume. Observe how volume decreased as

347
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:56,959
the pattern formed. The volume under the

348
00:14:54,000 --> 00:15:00,000
head is low compared to the rally that

349
00:14:56,959 --> 00:15:02,480
preceded it. In fact, volume is

350
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:05,839
extremely low on this bounce from the

351
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:08,320
neckline. Once the neckline was broken,

352
00:15:05,839 --> 00:15:11,279
volume began to increase as the price

353
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:13,519
moved lower. In fact, it started to

354
00:15:11,279 --> 00:15:16,639
increase prior to the breakout, which

355
00:15:13,519 --> 00:15:18,880
confirms the selling pressure.

356
00:15:16,639 --> 00:15:21,519
This also works if it's not a head and

357
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:24,160
shoulders. Maybe you have a triple top,

358
00:15:21,519 --> 00:15:26,720
which includes a liquidity run. The

359
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:29,279
neckline is the focal point if you wish

360
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:31,600
to use this pattern to your advantage.

361
00:15:29,279 --> 00:15:34,480
This is the area where many buyers

362
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:36,240
remain trapped with losing positions.

363
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:38,959
Since the price moved up from the

364
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:41,600
neckline on several occasions, we can

365
00:15:38,959 --> 00:15:44,639
assume that many traders were buying at

366
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:47,279
that level. We know that those buyers

367
00:15:44,639 --> 00:15:49,920
along with any buyers who entered at

368
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:52,240
higher levels and are still in the trade

369
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:54,800
will be holding losing positions if the

370
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:57,199
neckline should break. These losing

371
00:15:54,800 --> 00:16:00,480
traders will be forced to sell which

372
00:15:57,199 --> 00:16:02,480
should help push the price lower. Also,

373
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:05,600
aggressive traders will close long

374
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:08,320
positions and start to sell as the price

375
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:11,279
breaks through the neckline. This adds

376
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:14,560
momentum. Entering this phase, you must

377
00:16:11,279 --> 00:16:17,199
see increasing volume.

378
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:19,839
The double liquidity run pattern, also

379
00:16:17,199 --> 00:16:22,320
known as the master pattern, is another

380
00:16:19,839 --> 00:16:25,759
common smart money formation. It's a

381
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:28,959
trap to attract both buyers and sellers

382
00:16:25,759 --> 00:16:31,519
to take losing positions. First, price

383
00:16:28,959 --> 00:16:34,480
breaks a swing high, but then it quickly

384
00:16:31,519 --> 00:16:37,120
reverses, deceiving all buyers who took

385
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:38,959
the bait of the breakout. Amateurs will

386
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:41,199
enter what looks like an obvious

387
00:16:38,959 --> 00:16:44,000
breakout. Then the professionals will

388
00:16:41,199 --> 00:16:46,480
push the market back the other way. This

389
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:48,959
is the first liquidity run. The second

390
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:52,079
part of the pattern consists in another

391
00:16:48,959 --> 00:16:54,800
trap. Price will decrease and will break

392
00:16:52,079 --> 00:16:57,600
a swing low this time and trapping

393
00:16:54,800 --> 00:17:00,079
sellers on the wrong side. This is the

394
00:16:57,600 --> 00:17:03,120
second liquidity run designed to trap

395
00:17:00,079 --> 00:17:05,679
the weak hands in the market. very hard

396
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:08,079
to make money as a retail trader if you

397
00:17:05,679 --> 00:17:10,480
don't know what you're doing. If you

398
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:12,720
analyze this pattern, you'll observe it

399
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:16,079
contains three market phases:

400
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:18,720
contraction, expansion, and trend.

401
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:20,959
Firstly, we have the contraction phase.

402
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:23,280
This is when the market is setting up.

403
00:17:20,959 --> 00:17:25,919
The contraction phase occurs on low

404
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:28,960
institutional trading volume resulting

405
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:31,440
in mostly sideways movement. It's not an

406
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:33,919
ideal phase for trading, but a part of

407
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:36,720
retail traders are taking the bait

408
00:17:33,919 --> 00:17:39,840
hoping to catch a breakout. You'll often

409
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:42,960
see this phase during the Tokyo session.

410
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:44,960
Secondly, we have the expansion phase.

411
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:47,280
This seems like an exciting phase for

412
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:49,360
retail traders. Expansion is

413
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:52,000
characterized by a minor increase in

414
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:54,559
trading volume. The market becomes more

415
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:57,600
active, breaking previous highs and

416
00:17:54,559 --> 00:18:00,160
lows. Smart money takes advantage of

417
00:17:57,600 --> 00:18:03,200
this phase to accumulate positions at

418
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:06,000
discounted prices while inexperienced

419
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:08,880
traders often get caught in the whips

420
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:11,280
movements. It can be a challenging phase

421
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:14,799
because market breaks on both sides of

422
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:17,360
the range trapping most retail traders.

423
00:18:14,799 --> 00:18:19,200
Finally, we have the trend phase. This

424
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:21,679
is the phase where the market makes a

425
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:25,039
significant and aggressive move in one

426
00:18:21,679 --> 00:18:27,520
direction with increasing volume. During

427
00:18:25,039 --> 00:18:30,080
this phase, institutional traders use

428
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:33,200
the market's liquidity to exit their

429
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:35,919
previously accumulated positions.

430
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:38,880
These three phases complete one market

431
00:18:35,919 --> 00:18:40,880
cycle. Once they've played out, you can

432
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:44,320
expect the market to go through these

433
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:46,559
phases once again. One more example.

434
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:49,120
During the contraction phase, you'll see

435
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:52,160
periods of sideways movements. You'll

436
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:54,320
notice low institutional volume. As a

437
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:56,480
beginner, it's wise to avoid the

438
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:58,960
contraction phase.

439
00:18:56,480 --> 00:19:01,760
Then we have the expansion phase, the

440
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:05,600
double manipulation with two liquidity

441
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:07,840
runs. First, a breakout below the range.

442
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:11,039
As soon as they see the market breaking

443
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:13,919
down, retail traders start selling

444
00:19:11,039 --> 00:19:16,400
believing it will continue to decline.

445
00:19:13,919 --> 00:19:19,679
Then later, when they see the market

446
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:21,679
breaking up, they start buying, assuming

447
00:19:19,679 --> 00:19:24,000
it will rise further.

448
00:19:21,679 --> 00:19:26,799
However, what they fail to understand is

449
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:28,880
that smart money operates differently.

450
00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:32,400
They sell when the price is above

451
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:34,799
average and buy when it's below average.

452
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:37,200
If you look at the volume at the time of

453
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:40,480
the fake breakouts, you'll see that it's

454
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:41,919
low. Lastly, we have the trend phase

455
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:44,720
where we see the price move

456
00:19:41,919 --> 00:19:47,440
significantly and you'll notice a volume

457
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:50,559
increase during this phase. You cannot

458
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:52,880
control when or how these phases occur.

459
00:19:50,559 --> 00:19:55,039
But if you try to understand them, you

460
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:56,799
can improve your trading approach and

461
00:19:55,039 --> 00:19:58,880
have a better grasp of the market

462
00:19:56,799 --> 00:20:01,039
dynamics.

463
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:03,440
Now, let's go deeper with some advanced

464
00:20:01,039 --> 00:20:06,000
smart money patterns. First is the

465
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:08,480
accumulation one. Accumulation is

466
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:10,320
nothing but a sideways market activity

467
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:12,799
that happens after an extended

468
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:15,520
downtrend. This is the phase where smart

469
00:20:12,799 --> 00:20:17,360
money try to acquire positions without

470
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:20,240
moving the prices too much to the

471
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:22,799
upside. So let me explain why events

472
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:25,360
during accumulation. First we have the

473
00:20:22,799 --> 00:20:28,000
preliminary support. This is when a lot

474
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:30,960
of buying starts happening after a long

475
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:33,760
period of prices going down. The volume

476
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:37,280
increases and the difference between the

477
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:39,840
highest and the lowest prices widens.

478
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:41,679
Then we have the selling climax. This is

479
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:44,159
the point where the selling pressure

480
00:20:41,679 --> 00:20:46,320
reaches its peak and the difference

481
00:20:44,159 --> 00:20:49,919
between the highest and the lowest

482
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:52,960
prices widens even more. Riddle traders

483
00:20:49,919 --> 00:20:57,120
continue to sell but smart money start

484
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:59,600
buying at or near the bottom. Then we

485
00:20:57,120 --> 00:21:02,000
have the automatic rally. After the

486
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:04,720
intense selling pressure decreases,

487
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:07,840
there is a wave of buying that easily

488
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:10,080
pushes the prices up. This rally helps

489
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:13,120
us define the upper boundary of the

490
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:15,840
trading range during the accumulation.

491
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:18,400
Next is the secondary test. The price

492
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:20,559
revisits the level of the selling climax

493
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:23,840
to see if there is a balance between

494
00:21:20,559 --> 00:21:26,159
supply and demand at that level. For a

495
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:28,720
bottom to be confirmed, the volume

496
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:31,039
should be significantly lower as the

497
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:34,240
market approaches the support level

498
00:21:31,039 --> 00:21:36,799
around the selling climax area. And it's

499
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:39,120
common to have multiple secondary tests

500
00:21:36,799 --> 00:21:41,200
after a selling climax.

501
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:43,919
And then we have the sign of strength.

502
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:45,840
This happens when the price goes up with

503
00:21:43,919 --> 00:21:49,360
increasing price difference and

504
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:52,480
relatively higher trading volume. A sign

505
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:54,960
of strength often occurs after a spring,

506
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:57,760
which is a fake breakout, a liquidity

507
00:21:54,960 --> 00:22:00,559
run trapping retail traders on the short

508
00:21:57,760 --> 00:22:03,520
side. A spring is when the price falls

509
00:22:00,559 --> 00:22:07,120
below its usual range and then quickly

510
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:09,919
jumps back up into that range. And then

511
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:12,480
we have the last point of support. This

512
00:22:09,919 --> 00:22:15,679
is the lowest point during a pullback

513
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:18,000
after a sign of strength. It marks the

514
00:22:15,679 --> 00:22:20,480
final push toward the bottom of the

515
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:23,520
accumulation phase before the upward

516
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:26,159
trend begins. The last point of support

517
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:29,840
creates a higher low and then the price

518
00:22:26,159 --> 00:22:31,840
starts going up again aggressively.

519
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:34,559
Now let's analyze the different phases

520
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:38,080
of an accumulation taking into account

521
00:22:34,559 --> 00:22:40,000
the volume. First is the phase A. This

522
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:43,039
is where the sellers have been dominant

523
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:45,280
until now. We see a decrease in supply

524
00:22:43,039 --> 00:22:48,080
during the preliminary support and the

525
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:50,799
selling climax. These events are usually

526
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:54,240
obvious on the charts with wider price

527
00:22:50,799 --> 00:22:57,360
differences in high trading volume. In

528
00:22:54,240 --> 00:23:00,320
phase B, smart money start buying at

529
00:22:57,360 --> 00:23:02,960
relatively low prices in anticipation of

530
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:06,640
the next increase. The price swings are

531
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:08,720
wide with high trading volume. But as

532
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:10,960
smart traders absorb the available

533
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:13,679
supply, the volume during downward

534
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:15,280
swings within the trading range tends to

535
00:23:13,679 --> 00:23:17,840
decrease.

536
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:20,640
In phase C, the price goes through a

537
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:23,280
decisive test of the remaining supply to

538
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:26,320
determine if it's ready for an increase.

539
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:28,480
It's like a trap for those who sold. A

540
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:30,799
successful test of supply with the

541
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:34,400
spring provides a good opportunity to

542
00:23:30,799 --> 00:23:36,640
initiate a long position. In phase D,

543
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:39,280
demand starts dominating supply

544
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:42,720
consistently. we see a pattern of price

545
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:45,200
advances, signs of strength with wider

546
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:48,000
price differences and increasing trading

547
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:50,799
volume. There is also a last point of

548
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:54,240
support with smaller price differences

549
00:23:50,799 --> 00:23:56,880
and lower trading volume. And finally,

550
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:59,280
we have phase E. This is when the price

551
00:23:56,880 --> 00:24:02,400
leaves the trading range and demand

552
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:05,440
