618
00:26:56,640 --> 00:27:02,880
this phase. In phase D, signs of demand

619
00:27:00,559 --> 00:27:05,840
decrease and the price may break the

620
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:08,559
trading range support or decline below

621
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:11,039
the midpoint of the range. It's a good

622
00:27:08,559 --> 00:27:13,679
time to go short at the last point of

623
00:27:11,039 --> 00:27:16,480
supply. It's also the last opportunity

624
00:27:13,679 --> 00:27:20,080
for long position holders to close their

625
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:21,520
positions and go short. In phase E,

626
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:24,400
which is the final phase of

627
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:26,559
distribution, supply is in control and

628
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:28,880
price breaks below the trading range

629
00:27:26,559 --> 00:27:31,440
support.

630
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:34,799
The high volume supply breakout pattern

631
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:37,279
is one of my personal edges. When smart

632
00:27:34,799 --> 00:27:40,080
money push up through a potential area

633
00:27:37,279 --> 00:27:42,640
of supply which is known as a resistance

634
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:45,440
level, they face a challenge. Many

635
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:47,760
traders who bought within that area are

636
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:50,640
still holding their positions and want

637
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:52,640
to sell to recover their investments.

638
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:55,279
These traders represent potential

639
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:57,360
supply, meaning they can act as a

640
00:27:55,279 --> 00:28:00,559
resistance to the market's upward

641
00:27:57,360 --> 00:28:03,679
movement. If market makers are expecting

642
00:28:00,559 --> 00:28:06,240
higher prices and want a rally, they

643
00:28:03,679 --> 00:28:09,200
need to avoid being forced to buy from

644
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:12,480
these traders at what may seem like high

645
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:15,120
prices. So, they use a strategy called

646
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:17,520
gapping, which means quickly and

647
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:20,559
significantly pushing the price up

648
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:22,799
through the supply zone. By the way, I

649
00:28:20,559 --> 00:28:25,520
learned this from Tom Williams book,

650
00:28:22,799 --> 00:28:28,320
Master the Markets, a must readad if you

651
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:31,200
want to learn more about this. This

652
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:33,600
momentum candle on high volume

653
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:36,240
discourages the trap traders from

654
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:38,559
selling. As the market approaches the

655
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:40,960
point where these sellers can sell

656
00:28:38,559 --> 00:28:44,000
without a loss, the price suddenly

657
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:47,120
shoots up, often creating a gap on the

658
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:50,480
chart. This gives these traders a profit

659
00:28:47,120 --> 00:28:53,679
and reduces their inclination to sell.

660
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:56,799
Gapping up through supply on high volume

661
00:28:53,679 --> 00:28:59,600
is a tactic used by smart money to limit

662
00:28:56,799 --> 00:29:02,880
the amount they need to buy to sustain

663
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:06,320
the rally. It helps them avoid buying at

664
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:09,039
high prices. When high volume follows

665
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:11,120
this wide spreads, it indicates that

666
00:29:09,039 --> 00:29:14,000
professional traders were willing to

667
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:17,039
absorb the selling from the trap traders

668
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:19,600
who did decide to sell and this is known

669
00:29:17,039 --> 00:29:22,080
